Name: postinflammatory pulmonary fibrosis
Definition: A lung disease that is characterized by abnormal accumulation of surfactant occurs within the alveoli

Name: diffuse pulmonary fibrosis
Definition: A pulmonary fibrosis that is characterized by diffuse destruction
Synonym: malignant Giant cell neoplasm of soft Parts

Name: localized pulmonary fibrosis
Definition: A pulmonary fibrosis that is characterized by localized destruction
Synonym: malignant Giant cell neoplasm of soft Parts
